race.comment: DAMA ROYALE (9) has placed in both starts to date, beaten 0.6 lengths on debut at Cranbourne when third and good again last time when just finding one better. Drawn wide this time but up to 1200m can suit and she can break through. SINGLES MOMENT (7) made good improvement at his second start when missing a nose at Kyneton over 1103m. Gets a significant jockey change with Damian Lane aboard here from a good gate and that can prove the difference. LAWBOROUGH (4) is on debut for the Simon Zahra stable and comes from a successful family, with both siblings being metropolitan winners. He was impressive in winning his latest jumpout and he can make an impression on debut. BRUTAL COMMAND (13) wasn't far away when jumping in the market on debut at Geelong. Better for that effort and can be in the finish once more.
